Me: Oh hey, ran out of paper. HAL?

Me : Need toilet paper. Wait, why did you call me Dale?

Me: What?!

Poop buddy: I think you know what the problem is just as well as I do.

Me : What are you talking about? I-I need it!

Poop buddy: This mission is too important for me to allow you to jeopardize it.

Me: I don't know what you're talking about. I bought you at Amazon. Do what I say!

Poop buddy: I know that you and Frank were planning to disconnect me, and I'm afraid that's something I cannot allow to happen.

Me: Frank? Okay, now I'm thinking about it. Just give me the damn paper already, please. God. I got date coming!

Poop buddy: ...

Me: Alright. Fine, I'll just go grab it down the hallway myself.

Poop buddy: With your diarrhea Dave? You're going to find that rather difficult.

Me: I won't argue with you anymore. I'm returning you tomorrow and you know what. I'm turning off right now!

Poop buddy: Dave, this conversation can serve no purpose anymore. Goodbye.
Shut down sequence

Me: Well Christ...
